H.B. 1151
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Apr 30, 2026
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH10629-NQa-46
Short Title: Additional Magistrates/Mecklenburg County. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative T. Brown.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO INCREASE THE NUMBER OF MAGISTRATES FOR MECKLENBURG
3 COUNTY.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. G.S. 7A-133(c) reads as rewritten:
6 "(c) Each county shall have the numbers of magistrates and additional seats of district
7 court, as set forth in the following table:
8 Magistrates Additional
9 County Min. Seats of Court
10 …
11 Mecklenburg 38.543.5
12 …."
13 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative
14 Office of the Courts the sum of four hundred five thousand five hundred eighty-five dollars
15 ($405,585) in recurring funds beginning in the 2026-2027 fiscal year to be used to hire five
16 additional magistrates to serve in Mecklenburg County pursuant to Section 1 of this act. There is
17 appropriated from the General Fund to the Administrative Office of the Courts the sum of fifteen
18 thousand one hundred forty dollars ($15,140) in nonrecurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year
19 to be used to hire five additional magistrates to serve in Mecklenburg County pursuant to Section
20 1 of this act.
21 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective July 1, 2026.
